### ConnectHub — REST Client Test Suite (Complete)
### Base URL: http://localhost:9090/api/v1
###
### Usage:
###   VS Code  → install "REST Client" (humao.rest-client) → click "Send Request"
###   IntelliJ → open as HTTP file → click the green ▶ button
###
### Quick start:
###   1. Start docker compose (Postgres)
###   2. Run backend:  mvn spring-boot:run -Dspring-boot.run.profiles=postgres,dev
###   3. Run §2.9 (login alice), copy the token into @token
###   4. Run §2.11 (login bob),  copy the token into @bobToken
###   5. Execute requests top-to-bottom
###
### Seed users (DataSeeder — spring.profiles.active=postgres,dev):
###   alice / Password1!    bob / Password1!    carol / Password1!
###   dave  / Password1!    eve / Password1!

@baseUrl   = http://localhost:9090/api/v1
@token     = PASTE_ALICE_JWT_HERE
@bobToken  = PASTE_BOB_JWT_HERE
@carolToken= PASTE_CAROL_JWT_HERE

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 1. HEALTH
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 1.1 Health check (public endpoint)
GET {{baseUrl}}/health
Accept: application/json


# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 2. AUTH
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 2.1 Register — Alice ✅ (expect 201)
# @name registerAlice
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "alice",
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "Password1!",
  "displayName": "Alice Wonder"
}

###

### 2.2 Register — Bob ✅
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "bob",
  "email": "bob@example.com",
  "password": "Password1!",
  "displayName": "Bob Builder"
}

###

### 2.3 Register — Carol ✅
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "carol",
  "email": "carol@example.com",
  "password": "Password1!",
  "displayName": "Carol Danvers"
}

###

### 2.4 Register ❌ — short password (expect 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "baduser",
  "email": "bad@example.com",
  "password": "abc",
  "displayName": "Bad User"
}

###

### 2.5 Register ❌ — invalid email format (expect 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "bademail",
  "email": "not-an-email",
  "password": "Password1!",
  "displayName": "Bad Email"
}

###

### 2.6 Register ❌ — blank username (expect 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "",
  "email": "blank@example.com",
  "password": "Password1!",
  "displayName": "Blank User"
}

###

### 2.7 Register ❌ — duplicate username (expect 409)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "alice",
  "email": "alice2@example.com",
  "password": "Password1!",
  "displayName": "Alice Again"
}

###

### 2.8 Register ❌ — duplicate email (expect 409)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "alice999",
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "Password1!",
  "displayName": "Alice III"
}

###

### 2.9 Login by username ✅ — COPY returned token into @token above
# @name loginAlice
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "usernameOrEmail": "alice",
  "password": "Password1!"
}

###

### 2.10 Login by email ✅
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "usernameOrEmail": "alice@demo.com",
  "password": "Password1!"
}

###

### 2.11 Login — Bob ✅ — COPY token into @bobToken
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "usernameOrEmail": "bob",
  "password": "Password1!"
}

###

### 2.12 Login — Carol ✅ — COPY token into @carolToken
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "usernameOrEmail": "carol",
  "password": "Password1!"
}

###

### 2.13 Login ❌ — wrong password (expect 401)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "usernameOrEmail": "alice",
  "password": "WrongPassword!"
}

###

### 2.14 Login ❌ — non-existent user (expect 401)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "usernameOrEmail": "nobody_xyz_99999",
  "password": "Password1!"
}

###

### 2.15 Login ❌ — blank credentials (expect 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "usernameOrEmail": "",
  "password": ""
}


